Turkey Stocks: Acibadem, CarrefourSA, Ittifak, Sabanci, Turkcell

-- B y   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 
2011-09-23T15:47:08Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-23/altinyag-ittifak-turkcell-turk-telekom-turkey-stocks-preview.html
Turkey’s benchmark  ISE National 100
Index (XU100)  fell for a third day, dropping 1,656.52, or 2.9 percent,
to 56,323.38. That brings the gauge’s weekly drop to 2.7
percent.  The following stocks were active. Symbols are in
parentheses.  Acibadem Saglik Hizmetleri & Ticaret AS (ACIBD TI), a
Turkish hospitals chain in which Dubai-based Abraaj Capital Ltd.
is looking to sell a stake, jumped 1.15 liras, or 5.1 percent,
to 23.75 liras. Bids for the stake are due today, the Wall
Street Journal reported, citing unidentified people.  CarrefourSA Carrefour Sabanci Ticaret Merkezi AS (CARFA)  , the supermarket chain, jumped as much as 7.5 percent after
 Haci Omer Sabanci Holding AS (SAHOL)  , Turkey’s second-biggest
group of companies, denied a Reuters report which said it had
started buying more shares in the company from European parent
 Carrefour SA. (CA)  The shares closed up 10 kurus, or 0.7 percent, at
14.75 liras.  Sabanci shares dropped 28 kurus, or 4.4 percent, to 6.08
liras.  Ittifak Holding AS (ITTFH TI), a holding company with
interests in shopping centers, construction and livestock, added
14 kurus, or 1.9 percent, to 7.60 liras. The company said after
the market closed yesterday that it won a 93.8 million lira ($51
million) contract to build a stadium in the central Turkish city
of Konya.  Tat Konserve Sanayii AS (TATKS)  , a producer of canned
and frozen foods, surged as much as 10 percent before closing up
13 kurus, or 4.8 percent, at 2.82 liras. The company signed
agreements with real estate consultants to sell its 175,000
square meters of property in the Tuzla district outside
Istanbul.  Turkcell Iletisim Hizmetleri AS (TCELL TI),  Turkey ’s
largest mobile phone company, rose 6 kurus, or 0.7 percent, to
8.62 liras. The operator was raised to “neutral” from “sell”
at Goldman Sachs Group Inc.  To contact the reporter on this story:
